# rvv-simulator project context

Use this when working in this repo so you don't have to re-scan the codebase from scratch.

## What the project is

- RISC-V vector extension (v0.7) simulator in C++.
- No Boost; tests use Googletest (FetchContent). CMake >= 3.16.

## Layout

- **Headers**: `include/riscv/ext/` (e.g. `v.hpp`).
- **Core lib**: `src/riscv32/` (e.g. `v.cpp`) → static lib `riscv32`.
- **vstdlib**: `vstdlib/` → static lib `vstdlib` (memcpy, memset, memmove, etc.); links to `riscv32`.
- **Tests**: `tests/` — three executables: `unit_tests`, `vector_examples`, `stdlib`. CMake subdirs: `vstdlib/`, `tests/`.

## Build and test

- Configure: `cmake -S . -B build`
- Build: `cmake --build build`
- Googletest is fetched automatically (FetchContent). `gtest_discover_tests` is used so CTest sees each `TEST` / `TEST_P` individually.
- Run tests: `ctest --test-dir build` or run `build/tests/unit_tests`, `build/tests/vector_examples`, `build/tests/stdlib` directly.

## Test conventions

- Three test executables; shared helpers (`RandomBuf`, `RandomBufInt32`, `RandomBufChar`, `kBufSize`, etc.) live in anonymous namespaces in each test file.
- No fixtures unless tests need real shared state; prefer `TEST(Suite, name)` and helpers over duplicated setup.
- Prefer deduplication via shared helpers (see `tests/stdlib.cpp`, `tests/unit_tests.cpp`, `tests/vector_examples.cpp`). Avoid adding fixtures that only wrap a single helper.
